radiographic_examinations.findings: No evidence of metastatic disease. A 5.0-32.7-cm mass in the right axilla was seen, suggestive of right axillary lymphadenopathy.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: In May 2006, a computed tomographic scan demonstrated one new extrathoracic lymph node and slight enlargement of another. The other lymph nodes were stable.
